‚ÄúPower in Pain‚Äù has been on repeat for me as an #anthem to remind me of my self worth and to give me back my #confidence and take my #power back. So many of us are afraid to be ourselves and live our truth. This #song and #music video #Learn2Love is about the journey of self discovery and how it can make you feel lonely and isolated from everyone. Sometimes everything on the surface seems fine but below the surface is pain and you feel like you can‚Äôt breathe. Know that you‚Äôre not alone because I live that life for a very long time, afraid to be myself and what happens is you end up hurting everyone around you including yourself. It can take time for you to be ready to break through and have the strength to come out of darkness. I hope this song and video helps give you the confidence and strength to know your story can have a happy ending.
üßúüèº‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏èI am no longer afraid üßúüèº‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è
üåà Learn2Love is a sequel to my music video #Midnight and a prequel to my music video #SuperPower telling a true story of my life when I was in the closet. Most people don‚Äôt know I was actually in the closet til I was 28years old. I want to tell stories that helps anyone who is going through something that they are not alone and it‚Äôs ok to be afraid and when the timing is right they will find their identity and discover the magic of being theme selves.

Here is the result of Midnight Flame 7 on a darker starting level. When coloring hair red always consider the base and background contributing color that supports the end result. 
Midnight Flame 7 has a Copper/Red tone and if you apply it on lighter levels with less red underlying pigment you will see more copper. If you apply it on lower levels with more depth then you will see more red since lower levels has more red background. Always understand color theory so it helps you formulate to achieve your end result.
üß°Her starting level is level 3. So Permanent color was chosen to lift and deposit color. The best part is we also have a corresponding DEMI so you can enrich, glaze and gloss the hair for even more richness in tonality.
